text.headline: MAKING PIRACY! STOP IT 2006 A.D.
सारङ्गी रेटौला मौका मिले फेरी भेटौंला
GIRISH & THE UNITY PRESENTS X
थ्वयात हे मतिना धाइगु जुइ
RAJAMATI
text.text: Seturam Shrestha becomes the first Nepalese artist to record a song on a gramophone disc. Among the songs he recorded in a studio in Kolkata, India was the iconic Rajamati.

text.headline: MELBA DEVI GURUNG
text.text: Melba Devi Gurung becomes the first female artist to record a song done in Calcutta.

text.headline: GRAMOPHONE INVENTED
text.text: Thomas Edison with his second phonograph, photographed by Levin Corbin Handy in Washington, April 1878

text.headline: RADIO INVENTED
text.text: Guglielmo Marconi, an Italian inventor, who proved the feasibility of radio communication. He sent and received his first radio signal in Italy in 1895.

text.headline: NEPAL IS OPEN TO FOREIGNERS
text.text: End of Rana rule. Sovereignty of crown restored and anti-Rana rebels in Nepalese Congress Party form government. Nepal is officially open for foreigners.

text.headline: NEPAL IS DEMOCRATIZED
text.text: King Tribhuvan declared Nepal's first steps to democracy with a historical proclamation.

text.headline: RATNA RECORDING SANSTHAN FOUNDED
text.text: "King Mahendra founded Ratna Recording Sansthan, which paired with Radio Nepal to press records of Nepali national music."

text.headline: FIRST FILM OF NEPAL 'MAITIGHAR' RELEASED
text.text: Maitighar released becoming the first film of Nepal.

text.headline: ROYAL NEPAL FILM CORPORATION ESTABLISHED
text.text: The Nepal government established the Royal Nepal Film Corporation in 1971. Mann Ko Bandh was the first film produced by the corporation. Amber Gurung scored the background music.

text.headline: MUSIC NEPAL IS ESTABLISHED
text.text: Music Nepal is established under the Industrial Act of Nepal as the first music company of the country which pioneered the concept of royalty payment to the artists.

text.headline: FIRST NEPALI MUSIC VIDEO
text.text: First Nepali music video titled "Mayalu Timi Tadha" starring Bhuwan KC directed by Shambhujit Baskota.

text.headline: FM KATHMANDU
text.text: Radio Nepal launched the first FM Channel in Nepal - FM Kathmandu

text.headline: LONG PLAYING (LP) VINYL COMMERCIALLY AVAILABLE
text.text: RCA-Victor made the first Long Playing (LP) Vinyl commercially available. However, it would not be sought-after until 1948.

text.headline: BIRTH OF THE FIRST ELECTRIC GUITAR
text.text: Birth of the first electric guitar, Rickenbacker Frying Pan, invented by George Beauchamp and manufactured by Rickenbacker Electro. Similarly, the first electric guitar developed in the early 1930s.

text.headline: DEVELOPMENT OF STEREOPHONIC SOUND
text.text: Development of stereophonic sound by Bell Laboratories in New York. Walt Disney’s Fantasia (1940) was the first commercial studio film amplified by stereo sound.

text.headline: FIRST LP RECORD LAUNCHED
text.text: Columbia Records launches first LP records containing 45 minutes of music.

text.headline: FIRST HOME RECORDING DECKS SOLD
text.text: First consumer priced home recording decks using magnetic tapes are sold.

text.headline: BEATLES IN THE US
text.text: Arrival of Beatles in the US marks the beginning of the British Invasion & formation of British band, Pink Floyd.

text.headline: NORWEGIAN WOOD BY BEATLES
text.text: First commercial western music featuring sitar, Norwegian Wood by Beatles.

text.headline: RAVI SHANKAR PERFORMS AT MONTEREY INTERNATIONAL POP FESTIVAL
text.text: Monterey International Pop Festival where Ravi Shankar performed.

text.headline: NEPAL JOINS UNITED NATIONS
text.text: "Mahendra, ascends to the throne in 1955 and begins consolidating power. Nepal joins United Nations."

text.headline: EXILE OF DALAI LAMA
text.text: Exile of Dalai Lama led to over 20,000 Tibetan Refugees in Nepal.

text.headline: MAHENDRA TAKES OVER, DECLARES A STATE OF EMERGENCY
text.text: "Mahendra takes over, declares a state of emergency, suspends political parties and arrests BP Koirala and members of his cabinet."

text.headline: PANCHAYAT STARTED
text.text: "New constitution provides for non-party system of councils known as ""panchayat"" under which king exercises sole power. "

text.headline: KING MAHENDRA'S ONE NATION-ONE LANGUAGE POLICY
FIRST ELECTIONS TO RASTRYA PANCHAYAT HELD.
1854 MULUKI AIN (LAW OF LAND) IS REPLACED BY THE NEW MULUKI AIN
text.text: "The 1854 Muluki Ain (Law of Land) is replaced by the new Muluki Ain. The old Muluki Ain had stratified the society into rigid caste hierarchy and regulated all social interactions. The most notable feature was in punishment - the lower one's position in the hierarchy the higher the punishment for the same crime."

text.headline: DRUG (CONTROL) ACT 2033 CANNABIS ILLEGAL.
text.text: The narcotic Drug (control) Act 2033 made cannabis illegal.

text.headline: PANCHAYAT SYSTEM DISBANDED, CONSTITUTIONAL MONARCHY BEGAN
COMMUNIST PARTY OF NEPAL INITIATED AN INSURGENCY
text.text: Communist Party of Nepal initiated an insurgency

text.headline: NEPAL DECLARED FEDERAL DEMOCRATIC REPUBLIC
text.text: Constituent Assembly declared Nepal a Federal Democratic Republic, abolishing the 240 year-old monarchy

text.headline: KANTIPUR FM FIRST COMMERCIAL PRIVATE FM STATION
text.text: Kantipur FM becomes the first commercial private FM Station in the country after buying independent airing liscense.

text.headline: IMAGE FM 97.9 MHZ FOUNDED AS KATH FM WITH TRANSMISSION LIMITED TO KATHMANDU
text.text: Image FM 97.9 MHz founded as Kath FM with transmission limited to Kathmandu
